---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Netherlands Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/netherlands/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Belgium for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/belgium' },
  { title: 'Germany for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/germany' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'netherlandsFit', header: 'Netherlands Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€340-470/mo', netherlandsFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€400-580/mo', netherlandsFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€310-440/mo', netherlandsFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€290-410/mo', netherlandsFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Dutch Basisverzekering', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '€130-180/mo', netherlandsFit: 'Mandatory' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€310-470', annual: '€3,720-5,640' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€430-620', annual: '€5,160-7,440' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€580-850', annual: '€6,960-10,200' },
  { category: 'Dutch Basic Insurance', monthly: '€130-180', annual: '€1,560-2,160' },
  { category: 'Dutch Supplementary Insurance', monthly: '€20-100', annual: '€240-1,200' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in the Netherlands 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in the Netherlands. Basisverzekering system, Amsterdam hospitals, visa options, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in the Netherlands"
  subheadline="The Netherlands offers excellent healthcare, English proficiency, and high quality of life—with mandatory insurance providing universal access."
  heroImage="/images/countries/netherlands-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose the Netherlands</h2>
  <p>
    The Netherlands consistently ranks among the world's best countries for quality of life, healthcare, and expat friendliness. Nearly everyone speaks excellent English, making it one of the easiest European countries for English-speaking retirees.
  </p>

  <p>
    Amsterdam offers world-class culture and excellent healthcare facilities. The Hague provides an international atmosphere with embassies and tribunals. Rotterdam is modern and architecturally interesting. Smaller cities like Utrecht, Leiden, and Maastricht offer charm with lower costs.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; ranked top 10 in Europe</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Dutch official; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €2,200-3,800/month; Amsterdam most expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mild but rainy; cool summers, cold winters</li>
      <li><strong>Public Transport:</strong> Excellent trains, trams, and buses</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member; Schengen zone</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Netherlands Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    The Netherlands has a mandatory health insurance system. All residents must purchase basic health insurance (basisverzekering) from private insurers. The government regulates coverage and pricing, ensuring everyone has access regardless of health status.
  </p>

  <p>
    Basic insurance covers GP visits, hospital care, prescriptions, and mental health services. Many add supplementary insurance (aanvullende verzekering) for dental, physiotherapy, and other extras. The system is known for efficiency and quality.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Mandatory Deductible</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Dutch basic insurance has a mandatory annual deductible (eigen risico) of €385 (2026). You pay this before insurance kicks in for most care (GP visits and some preventive care are exempt). You can choose a higher voluntary deductible for lower premiums.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Non-EU seniors have several pathways to Dutch residency:
  </p>

  <h3>Financially Independent Persons Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees with sufficient passive income (typically €1,500-2,000/month). Must demonstrate you won't work in the Netherlands and have comprehensive health insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>Family Reunification</h3>
  <p>
    If you have Dutch citizen or resident family members, family reunification provides a pathway. Income and accommodation requirements apply.
  </p>

  <h3>EU Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    EU/EEA citizens can move freely. Register with the municipality (gemeente) and enroll in Dutch health insurance. Income requirements are minimal for EU citizens.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    The Netherlands has strict insurance requirements:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa application:</strong> Comprehensive international insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>After registration:</strong> Must enroll in Dutch basisverzekering within 4 months</li>
    <li><strong>Penalty for late enrollment:</strong> 130% premium surcharge for uninsured period</li>
    <li><strong>All ages accepted:</strong> Insurers cannot refuse anyone for basic insurance</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Netherlands</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Most expats use international insurance for the visa, then transition to Dutch basisverzekering after registration. The Dutch system is comprehensive and affordable. Many maintain international coverage for travel and home country visits.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors moving to the Netherlands, these providers offer strong initial coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Netherlands</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Dutch hospital network, 24/7 English support</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), strong European coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive pricing, good for DACH/Benelux region</li>
    <li><strong>Dutch Basisverzekering:</strong> Mandatory after residency; affordable and comprehensive</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Netherlands.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in the Netherlands are reasonable once you're in the Dutch system:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Transition quickly:</strong> Dutch basic insurance is much cheaper than international</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductible:</strong> Choosing €885 vs €385 deductible saves ~€200/year</li>
    <li><strong>Skip extras:</strong> If healthy, basic insurance may be sufficient</li>
    <li><strong>Compare annually:</strong> You can switch Dutch insurers each January</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Moving to Amsterdam with $3,000/month pension. Wants comprehensive coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for visa. After registration, enroll in Dutch basisverzekering. Keep Cigna (Netherlands excluded) for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~€380/month. After transition: Dutch €150/month + Cigna €200/month (reduced).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, moving to The Hague. One has heart condition.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global initially. Dutch system covers pre-existing once enrolled. Transition within 4 months.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€1,000/month combined initially. Dutch system: ~€320/month combined (both covered regardless of health).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: German Citizen, 69</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> EU citizen moving from Frankfurt to Utrecht. Currently in German GKV.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EHIC covers initial period. Register and enroll in Dutch basisverzekering.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Dutch basic ~€150/month. Much simpler than German dual system.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Will I be accepted for Dutch insurance with pre-existing conditions?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes. Dutch insurers must accept everyone for basic insurance regardless of health status. Premiums are community-rated (same price for everyone). This makes the Netherlands excellent for seniors with health conditions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I really need to speak Dutch?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For daily life, no. The Netherlands has the highest English proficiency in non-English speaking Europe. Most doctors, especially in cities, speak excellent English. Administrative documents are in Dutch, but translation services are available.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How quickly must I get Dutch insurance?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Within 4 months of registering with your gemeente (municipality). If you're late, you'll face a 130% premium surcharge and may be auto-enrolled. It's best to arrange insurance promptly after registration.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about dental care?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Basic insurance doesn't cover dental care for adults (only extractions). Most people add supplementary insurance (aanvullende verzekering) for dental, typically €20-50/month for basic dental coverage.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Netherlands.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Dutch authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
